complaints.title: Damaged Roads and Waterlogging near Kanke Road, Pandra Chowk
complaints.details:
Residents and daily commuters around Kanke Road, particularly near Pandra Chowk and the approach to CMPDI Gate, are struggling with poor road and drainage conditions.

Key issues observed:

Damaged Road Surface: Multiple deep potholes along the stretch cause traffic congestion and frequent two-wheeler accidents.

Waterlogging: During rainfall, clogged roadside drains lead to waterlogging, with knee-deep water making the area inaccessible.

Public Safety Concerns: Stagnant water near Pandra Chowk has become a breeding ground for mosquitoes, raising fears of dengue and malaria.

Traffic Disruptions: Autos and buses are forced to divert, worsening traffic jams in peak hours.

complaints.title: Irregular Drinking Water Supply at Doranda, Ward 32 (near St. Annes School)
complaints.details:
Residents of Doranda, Ward 32, especially those living in the locality around St. Annes School and Doranda Bazar Road, are facing irregular water supply for the past two weeks.

Key observations:

Water supply is limited to once every two days, and even then, the pressure is very low.

Families are forced to rely on private water tankers, adding to their expenses.

Schools and small shops in the area are struggling with sanitation due to lack of clean water.

Elderly residents and low-income families are the most affected, as they cannot afford alternate water sources.

Local complaints have been made to the water supply office, but no improvement has been noted.

complaints.title: Broken Public Toilets at Albert Ekka Chowk
complaints.details:
The public toilet complex near Albert Ekka Chowk, one of Ranchis busiest intersections, has been in a severely neglected condition for more than a month.

Key observations:

Out of 10 toilet units, only 3 are functional; others have broken doors, leaking taps, and no running water.

Hygiene standards are poor  overflowing septic tanks and foul odor deter people from using the facility.

Women and elderly citizens are especially affected, as there are no safe and clean alternatives nearby.

Vendors and daily commuters report open urination around the chowk due to lack of usable facilities, creating both sanitation and image problems for the city center.

Despite being located in a high-visibility area, no maintenance team has been deployed recently.

complaints.title: Neglected Childrens Park at Morabadi Ground
complaints.details:
The childrens park located near Morabadi Ground, opposite Birsa Munda Football Stadium, has been poorly maintained for several months, making it unsafe and unusable for families.

Key observations:

Several play equipment (swings, slides, see-saws) are broken or rusted, posing a danger to children.

The parks fencing is damaged, allowing stray animals to enter freely.

Grass and weeds are overgrown, reducing open play space.

Lighting inside the park is inadequate, leaving dark spots after sunset.

Despite repeated requests from local residents associations, no maintenance work has been carried out.
